TI  - A Meta-Framework for Conducting an Integrated Mixed Methods Autoethnography
AU  - Anthony J. Onwuegbuzie
AU  - Madeline L. Abrams
AU  - Sandra Schamroth Abrams
AU  - Anna S. CohenMiller
AU  - Anthony Bambrola
AB  - This article is dedicated to the late Michael D. Fetters--a giant in the world of mixed methods research, an exceptional researcher and scholar, a professor of family medicine, a caring and beloved family physician, a lifelong learner, a colleague, a mentor, a steadfast advocate, a son, a sibling, a husband, a father, and, above all, a dear friend to everyone who knew him. Inspired by Professor Fetters's innovation, we offer an expanded definition of autoethnography through the formal introduction of the 10 dimensions of autoethnography, as well as the debut of mixed methods autoethnography and of integrated mixed methods autoethnography. An autoethnographic narrative writing style honors both the research genre and the mixed methods researchers' voices.
